	(text "Notes:\n1. PWM inputs typical signal behaviour is either off state or 100-115 kHz 50% duty cycle square wave.\n2. VCC should be between 13-16V.\n3. Dangerous scenario if PWM inputs are too high/low frequencies.\n4. N-mos gates include ESD protection."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 178.308 172.72 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.254)
				(bold yes)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "0914cfa2-634a-43f4-9620-cf4acf96fd2e")
	)
	(text "Emitter Drivers"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 144.272 123.952 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "4581a86e-048c-454d-9a3d-a07c4f1a15ed")
	)
	(text "Dsub 15 connector with power, GND and PWM inputs"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 55.118 176.022 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "9e61cc92-f4ff-4f87-b00e-40d5f1adc2d5")
	)
	(text "Discarded circuit ideas:\n1. Complex emitter driver circuit (ideal sine wave for ideal driving)\n2. BP filter on input to act as protection from too low or too high frequencies \n(it will distort the pwm signal which would aquire a shcmitt trigger to restore the vertical square wave edges which makes it more complex and costly)\n3. Removed ESD protection on Dsub input since mosfet gates already have integrated esd protection. \nThe power line doesn't need esd protection since it's not going to any sensitive components.\n4. SC protection with PPTC or fuse (could not find an ideal component)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 127 138.684 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "b1c746be-50c8-49ab-b3ed-678b04bec060")
	)
	(text "Power Indicator Diode"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 105.918 164.846 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "ff52c17e-7906-4280-beec-a357ccc1469f")
	)
